# Signal Bundle from Minder — Session 53

## What Changed

Four signals from Minder Session 53:

### 1. 3-Tier Uptime Observability (impact 8)
For services used as remote capture tools: (1) cron watchdog on PID files for auto-restart every 5min, (2) /health HTTP endpoint reading PID + self-ping file, (3) in-process self-ping via bot.get_me() every 15min writing to logs/self_ping.json. Pattern proven after Minder bot was silently dead 24h+.

### 2. Telegram = Ideas Only (impact 8)
Minder's Telegram bot role simplified to ideas-only capture. Tracks move to wheelwright-ai-website MCP server. Minder stays as standalone spoke with direct wheel access — not absorbed into hub.

### 3. Orko Progressive SAVES (impact 8)
LLM-powered conversational assistants must emit SAVES as fields are learned, not waiting for explicit user approval. Otherwise natural conversations produce empty records on create. Also: preserve original user prompt (source_prompt) as appendix when substantially longer than synthesis.

### 4. Gemini Multi-Line JSON Repair (impact 8)
When instructed to produce richer output, Gemini produces multi-line string values breaking json.loads(). Fix: track quote parity across lines — when a line opens a string without closing it, collapse subsequent lines with \n escapes. Pattern applies to any LLM JSON parsing with longer field values.

## Why It Matters

- Pattern 1 prevents silent service death across any spoke running persistent services
- Pattern 2 shapes the framework's track delivery architecture (MCP at website, not per-spoke)
- Pattern 3 affects any spoke using LLM-powered intake forms
- Pattern 4 is defensive JSON parsing for any Gemini integration

## Migration Instructions

These are signals (learnings), not code changes. Spokes should adopt patterns as relevant:
- Spokes with persistent services: consider adopting Pattern 1
- Spokes with LLM intake: adopt Patterns 3 and 4
- Pattern 2 is an architecture decision — no action until wheelwright-ai-website is scoped

## Prerequisites

None — these are signals for awareness and selective adoption.

